{"type":"message","id":"8b1ac8e3","parentId":"4283edba","timestamp":"2026-04-14T01:47:58.650Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. For the full deployment:\n\n1. **Backend** needs:\n   - MongoDB (localhost:27017)\n   - Redis (localhost:6379)\n   - .env configured\n   - Port 5555\n\n2. **Frontend** needs:\n   - Clone from GitLab\n   - Configure API URL pointing to backend\n   - Start on port 3000\n\nLet me spawn two agents in parallel: one for BE setup/start, one for FE clone+setup. This is a bigger task so I'll spawn properly.\n\nActually, let me do it more efficiently - spawn two parallel subagents.","thinkingSignature":"93f501227556ccf70d001c82b1343caa89bb3e5ba45b8a487a7341cc2de8f460"},{"type":"text","text":"Spawning 2 agent song song: **Backend** + **Frontend**.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dj8v4zm8xxmb_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are senior-backend. Deploy and start the full DTLX Backend system.\n\n## Context\n- Workspace: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend\n- Label: dtlx:deploy-be\n- This is for LOCAL deployment (not Docker)\n\n## Steps\n\n### 1. Check dependencies\n- cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend\n- Check if MongoDB is running: curl -s http://localhost:27017 2>/dev/null && echo \"MongoDB OK\" || echo \"MongoDB not running\"\n- Check if Redis is running: redis-cli ping 2>/dev/null || echo \"Redis not running\"\n- Check yarn: yarn --version\n\n### 2. Setup environment\n- If .env does NOT exist: cp .env.example .env\n- If .env exists: check MONGODB_URI points to correct DB\n- yarn install\n\n### 3. Seed data\n- yarn seed\n- Verify it completed successfully\n\n### 4. Build (required before start)\n- yarn build\n- If build fails: report error and STOP\n\n### 5. Start server\n- Start using: yarn dev  (runs nodemon src/server.ts)\n- Wait for server to start\n- Verify: curl http://localhost:5555/ping\n- Report server URL and status\n\n### 6. Smoke test key endpoints\n- GET /api/v1/auth/login (should return method not allowed or similar since it's POST - just verify endpoint exists)\n- Report all results\n\n## Rules\n- NEVER push or commit code\n- Read-only setup\n- Keep server RUNNING after setup (do NOT kill it)","label":"dtlx:deploy-be","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-backend","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend","runTimeoutSeconds":600,"mode":"run","cleanup":"delete"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dj8v4zm8xxmb_2","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are senior-frontend. Clone and deploy the full DTLX Frontend system.\n\n## Context\n- Workspace target: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/\n- GitLab: https://gitlab.com/ahv-dtlx/ahv-dtlx-frontend\n- Project ID: 77055851\n- Label: dtlx:deploy-fe\n\n## Steps\n\n### 1. Clone repo if not exists\n- Check if ahv-dtlx-frontend already exists in /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/\n- If NOT exists: git clone https://gitlab.com/ahv-dtlx/ahv-dtlx-frontend.git\n- If exists: cd into it and git pull origin develop\n\n### 2. Setup\n- cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend\n- Check package.json exists\n- Check .env or .env.local\n- yarn install\n\n### 3. Configure API URL\n- Check what API URL the frontend uses (src/services/, src/lib/, .env)\n- Update to point to http://localhost:5555 (DTLX Backend)\n- Check NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL or similar in .env.local\n\n### 4. Build\n- yarn build\n- If build fails: report error and STOP\n\n### 5. Start\n- Start dev server: yarn dev\n- Wait for \"Ready\" or \"started\"\n- Verify: curl http://localhost:3000\n- Report server URL and status\n\n## Rules\n- NEVER push or commit code\n- Read-only setup\n- Keep server RUNNING after setup","label":"dtlx:deploy-fe","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-frontend","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/works